title: Wolves drop three-set volleyball match at Evergreen State
text: Print this article Advertisement OLYMPIA â€” Walla Walla University dropped three straight sets, 25-15, 25-21 and 25-22, at Evergreen State College on Sunday. Maria Darling scored 14 kills and made 11 defensive digs for the Wolves (5-10 overall, 2-8 in Cascade Collegiate Conference play), while Lexi Shanko had 10 digs and Alissa Casey contributed 18 assists. The Wolves managed to make a strong run in the third set, reeling off 10 straight points, nine on Morgan Doyle serves. Darling recorded four of her kills during the surge. The run enabled Walla Walla to take a 17-11 lead, but the Evergreen State rebounded to win the set and wrap up their match victory. Walla Walla next plays Sunday at Warner Pacific.
